    <string name="type_of_set_desc">There are three types of set:\n\n1) Weight: Lifting a specific weight for a designated number of repetitions.\n\n2) Repetition: A set with a certain number of repetitions without a specific weight.\n\n3) Time: It is used to measure time execution of the reps.</string>
    <string name="statistics_desc">- Time elapsed refers to the total duration of the workout session.\n\n- The date indicates when the workout was finished.\n\n- Volume is defined as the total amount of weight lifted during a workout, calculated by multiplying for each completed set the number of repetitions performed by the weight lifted. Higher volume is associated with greater muscle hypertrophy and strength gains over time.\n\n- Exercises represent the total count of exercises included in this workout.\n\n- Total sets refers to the cumulative number of sets planned for each exercise in a workout. A set is a group of consecutive repetitions performed without resting.\n\n- Completed sets indicates the number of sets that were finished as planned by the workout.</string>
